[
  "Brothers James and Thomas Duff founded and co-own Duff Capital Investors, a holding company with total revenue of more than $2.6 billion. ",
  "They inherited commercial tire dealer Southern Tire Mart, Duff Capital's largest investment, from their father, Ernest Duff, who founded it in 1973. ",
  "In 2007, the Duffs started Duff Capital, through which they have made multiple acquisitions. ",
  "Over the years, Duff Capital has acquired trucking company KLLM, construction firm T.L. Wallace Construction and energy firm DeepWell Energy Services.",
  "Tom was appointed by Mississippi Governor Phil Bryant to represent the Second (Southern) Supreme Court District in May 2015."
]